{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_76","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the composition-loop end-to-end coverage in [backend/tests/test_story_tools.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/tests/test_story_tools.py) and documented it in [docs/composition-loop-e2e-test.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/composition-loop-e2e-test.md). The new scenario covers segmented writing, realtime chunk replay from a saved cursor, mid-segment pause, durable draft snapshot recovery, resume, and final story compilation. While adding it, the test exposed a real replay bug in [backend/app/services/session_hydration.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/services/session_hydration.py), so I fixed hydration to preserve `accepted_story_so_far` and related composition job metadata across recent-event replay.\n\nVerification completed:\n- `ruff check backend/app/services/session_hydration.py backend/tests/test_story_tools.py`\n- `cd backend && pytest tests/test_story_tools.py -k composition_loop_e2e` -> `1 passed`\n- `cd backend && pytest tests/test_story_tools.py tests/test_session_hydration_service.py` -> `40 passed`\n- `cd backend && pytest tests/test_session_api.py -k \"session_realtime_service_streams_composition_chunk_deltas or session_realtime_service_suppresses_initial_chunk_baseline or hydrate_session_endpoint_replays_context_updates_into_resumed_snapshot or hydrate_session_endpoint_preserves_chat_navigation_bridge_history\"` -> `4 passed`\n\nNo browser checks were needed because this was backend-only. The required reviewer summary is written to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/69_composition_loop_end_to_end_test/summary.md)."}}
